er Arab tradition in folk narrative. Speak, Bird, Speak Again is an essential guide to Palestinian culture and a must for those who want to deepen their understanding of a troubled, enduring people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFolk literature, ArabicxTranslations into EnglishxPalestinexMiddle EastxPalestine. 0aFolk literature, ArabiczPalestinevTranslations into English. 0aPalestinian ArabsvFolklore. 0aPalestinian ArabsxFolklore. 0aTalesxPalestine. 0aTaleszPalestine. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Folklore & Mythology.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aarab.  aarabs.  abridegrooms.  abrides.  acourtship.  acreation myths.  aenvironment.  afairy tales.  afiction.  afolk narrative.  afolklore.  afolktales.  agalilee.  agaza.  agender.  ahusbands and wives.  aislam.  alove.  amiddle east literature.  amiddle east.  amotif index.  amythology.  anature.  anonfiction.  aoral tradition.  apalestine.  apalestinian arab.  apalestinian culture.  apalestinian folktales.  apalestinian studies.  aparenting.  aromance.  asexuality.  asocial science.  astorytelling.  atypology.  awest bank.1 aDundes, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanaana, Sharif, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052090873440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520908734423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520908734/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles